<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="352" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="6.[1468,2678,278,907]" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1470,1816,672,705]" pageId="6" pageNumber="352">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Data Deficient on The [UCN Red List. There are no estimates of global population size of Perrin’s Beaked Whale. Like other species of beaked whales, Perrin’s Beaked Whale is potentially affected by ingestion of plastic debris, bycatch in driftnetfisheries, and noise pollution. Nevertheless, nothing is known about the form or extent of these potential impacts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
